      working in primary care as a diagnostic tool providing earlier and more precise 
      diagnoses. However, ultrasonography is a user-dependent technology and obtaining 
      competence requires both training and practice. Today, there is no consensus 
      about which ultrasound training GPs should have before they start scanning 
      patients in their clinics.
